{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, foundation models, due to their vast size and generalized pretraining, provide significant adaptability and scalability for a variety of tasks.",
    "Integrating these technologies poses unique challenges but also opens up exciting opportunities for innovation in AI training and application.",
    "This section explores the relationship between federated learning and foundation models, highlighting key research directions and recent advancements in this domain.",
    "Depending on the training paradigm, foundation models can either be trained from scratch or fine-tuned on top of pre-trained models within a federated learning framework.",
    "Additionally, the application of foundation models in federated learning can extend to large language models or vision language models."
  ]
}